                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d810">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.113 (Manchuria) Petroleum/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="from"
                        >Grew</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-09T23:00:00+09:00"
                            >December 9, 1933—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 9—12:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>187. Department’s telegram No. 98, October 20, 5 p.m.<note n="53"
                        xml:id="d810fn53">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The local office of the Socony Vacuum Corporation states that the Dairen
                        customs continues its discrimination in favor of Japanese kerosene.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>In view of the emphasis placed by Hirota on open-door policy in Manchuria
                        I believe it might be helpful to talk over this situation with British in
                        all frankness on the ground that local representations to “Manchukuo”
                        authorities do not appear to have produced favorable results. The Legation
                        at Peiping concurs.</item>
                    <pb facs="0844" n="742" xml:id="pg_742"/>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>It would presumably be necessary to leave with the Minister a written
                        memorandum or <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> to explain the technical
                        details.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Please instruct.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
